runs.text:
72 Seasons is the eleventh studio album by American heavy metal band Metallica, released on April 14, 2023, by their own record label Blackened Recordings. 72 Seasons was produced by Greg Fidelman, who produced the band's previous studio album, Hardwired... to Self-Destruct, and is the band's second studio album to be released through Blackened.
The album generally received positive reviews from critics, who mostly praised Hetfield's lyrics and vocal performance but criticized the album's length. In 2024, 72 Seasons received three nominations at the 66th Grammy Awards, winning Best Metal Performance for the title track "72 Seasons".
72 Seasons includes Metallica's longest original song to date, "Inamorata", which runs for over 11 minutes. The medley cover song "Mercyful Fate" on Garage, Inc. runs one second longer.
